id: pm-iv1u
title: "CI: skip non-source jobs on docs-only changes"
description: "Currently any docs/README/CHANGELOG edit triggers the full 5-matrix CI run (~60 GitHub-minutes). Add paths-ignore to CI push trigger for ['docs/**', '**/*.md', 'CHANGELOG.md', 'CONTRIBUTING.md', '.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/**'] OR use a fast 'paths' filter job that conditionally skips build-test. Keep PR-side strict so docs PRs still get a smoke run for confidence."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: ci,paths-filter,performance,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-16T22:07:41.048Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T11:30:57.131Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: Docs-only push to main skips build-test entirely or runs only a 1-job smoke validate; PRs still run a minimal check for safety; release.yml and nightly.yml unaffected.
parent: pm-tzwy
resolution: Push workflow now ignores docs-only paths while pull_request remains strict.
expected_result: Docs-only pushes skip expensive CI matrix work without weakening PR validation or release/nightly gates.
actual_result: Main workflow includes docs paths-ignore and contract assertions; latest main run is green with unchanged PR/release/nightly behavior.
